Master Answer:
Human Papillomavirus (HPV9) vaccine is part of BC's publicly funded (free) immunization program for those who are eligible and available from local health units, most pharmacies and some doctors' offices. For those not eligible for the publicly funded program, the vaccine can be purchased from travel health clinics, most pharmacies and some doctors' offices.
Immunization Nurse
